President Obama participated in a video conference with Afghan President Ashraf Ghani to discuss recent progress in Afghanistan. They praised the National Unity Government's efforts in naming candidates for key positions and discussed ways to strengthen security cooperation and the Afghan National Defense and Security Forces. They also discussed regional cooperation and the reconciliation process with the Taliban. Both leaders expressed their intentions to reaffirm international support for Afghanistan's peace and stability at upcoming summits. They also recommitted to regular consultations as the United States continues to support Afghanistan's government.